snippet.textDisplay: This song is all about life : " Par chanaa de " , like consoling your heart in difficult times , " Raat haneri nadi thatha maar di " , that this time is so difficult, you are haunted by things around you then " kachi Meri mitti kacha Mera Naam ni  han mei nakam ni " , it's about accepting your situation and saying, yes this is me , this is my life and I accept it and then " yaar nu milegi Aj laash yar di "  that you loose everything in your life and it's a goodbye to  any expectations from this worldly life and then paar chana de , you still consoling your heart with these words. I've had a very difficult time this year and whenever I listen to this song , I feel it's about me like I want to console myself and accept my situation. This was my theory I've heard the story behind this song about clay pot . Such a nice way of conveying it. Beautiful 🫠
